Sampson Itode, Port Harcourt The Police in Rivers State attached to the state task force on illegal street trading and motor parks on Sunday arrested four suspected hoodlums who attacked its operatives at the Ikokwu axis of Ikwerre Road in Port Harcourt, the state capital. The four suspects, according to the Coordinator of the taskforce, Felix Nwadibeyi, were in the habit of attacking members of the taskforce whenever they were operating around their territory. Nwadibeyi, told The PUNCH that the suspects were nabbed following a sting operation by the taskforce police and handed over to the state police command for interrogation and prosecution Nwadibeyi said, “Around 9am today, (Sunday) I went out with about three vehicles and when we saw those boys in one uncompleted filling station, we swung into action and got four of them arrested. They are now in the police net; they would be arraigned before the Magistrate’s Court any moment.” When contacted for confirmation, the spokesman of the Rivers State Police Command, Nnamdi Omoni, said he had yet to get the report on the incident, but promised to get back to our correspondent once he did. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 